Raul Gamsu, CEO of Consolidated Infrastructure Group (CIG) &#8211; which has a footprint in 21 African countries, and has grown from making $10million to $100 million in the past six years on the continent &#8211; chatted to us on the sidelines of the Moneyweb Into Africa roundtable discussion sponsored by Standard Bank. He talks through some of the opportunities, requirements of doing business in Africa, and risks to avoid. &#8220;You have the benefit of a population of 960 million which will soon be 1.6 billion &#8211; with that kind of pop growth and we anticipate that 65% of all the groups are going to be living in cities, huge megacities, the need for infrastructure in immense,&#8221; he predicts.This article is part of a series sponsored by Standard Bank Business Banking. Should you require further information about doing business in the rest of the continent please e-mail Moneyweb MD Marc Ashton with details of your project and he will connect you with an appropriate banking resource.